                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2e" xml:id="a2e">
                     
                     <locus>(fols. 247v–251r)</locus> 
                     <title>Theological extracts</title>
                     <note>anonymous collection of theological
                        excerpts from various authors; those named are <persName>Isaac</persName>,
                        <persName>Nicetas bp. of Serrae</persName>, <persName>&lt;Theodore&gt; Balsamon</persName>,
                        <persName>Maximus &lt;Confessor&gt;</persName>, <persName>Neilus Monachus</persName>, <persName>Marcus &lt;Monachus&gt;
                           Thalassius</persName>, <persName>Basilius Magnus</persName> (excerpts of the letters). Also there are
                    some chapters from a Gerontikon and in the margin of fol. 248v a later owner
                    wrote οἶμαι ὅτι τοῦ Νύϲϲηϲ.</note>
                     <incipit>τὴν ἁγίαν κοινωνίαν καλοῦϲιν ἕνωϲιν <note>(first excerpt, anonymous)</note></incipit>
